{{Quote|It worked fine when you tested it initially. Synthetic?''"<br />"''Kubaz xurkonia. The crystalline latice handled the energy while we tested it, but it was probably ready to go down anytime.|Elegos A'Kla and Corran Horn|<ref name="I, Jedi">''[[I, Jedi]]''</ref>}}
'''Kubaz xirkonia''' was a type of mineral that was used in the creation of fake [[Diamond/Legends|diamonds]].

[[Corran Horn/Legends|Corran Horn]] used a kubaz xirkonia gemstone during the construction of [[Corran Horn's lightsaber|his]] [[Dual-phase lightsaber/Legends|dual-phase lightsaber]], although at the time he believed it was a diamond. Although the gem held up during testing, it burned out a short time later during a confrontation with [[Shala]] the [[Hutt/Legends|Hutt]]. Corran later replaced it with a real diamond.

==Behind the scenes==
The name is spelled "xirkonia" in ''[[Star Wars: Mara Jade – By the Emperor's Hand]]'' and "xurkonia" in ''[[I, Jedi]]''. Both sources were authored by [[Michael A. Stackpole]].

